      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): warn when toolsAllow includes web_search but no search provider is enabled",
        "body": "Closes #97654\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where operators configuring a cron job with `toolsAllow: [\"web_search\"]` would experience silent failure when all web search provider plugins were disabled. The job ran to completion with `status: ok` and `lastDeliveryStatus: delivered`, but the output was the model apologising that it could not search — no warning appeared in `cron_run_logs.diagnostics_summary` or `openclaw logs`.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`toolsAllow` gates whether a *registered* tool is permitted; it does not validate whether the tool is *registered* at all. When all search plugins are disabled, `webSearchProviders = []` and the `web_search` tool is never added to the registry, but nothing signals this mismatch to the operator.\n\nThe fix adds a preflight check in `prepareCronRunContext` (called before the agent turn is dispatched): after runtime plugins are loaded, if the resolved `toolsAllow` contains `\"web_search\"` (or `\"*\"`) and `listWebSearchProviders()` returns an empty list, a `warn`-severity diagnostic entry is produced. This diagnostic is merged into the final run result via `mergeCronRunDiagnostics`, so it appears in `diagnostics_summary` regardless of whether the run status is `\"ok\"` or `\"error\"`.\n\nThe check is a read-only preflight with no behaviour change to the execution path; it does not block the run.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators whose cron jobs include `web_search` in `toolsAllow` but have no search provider plugin enabled will now see a warning in `diagnostics_summary`:\n\n```\nweb_search tool requested (toolsAllow) but no web search provider plugin is enabled. Enable one with: openclaw plugins enable duckduckgo\n```\n\nThis makes the misconfiguration visible without altering run status or blocking execution. Jobs that have a provider enabled are not affected.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Modified file:** `src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts`\n\nKey logic added in `prepareCronRunContext` (runs after `ensureRuntimePluginsLoaded`):\n\n```ts\nconst agentPayloadToolsAllow = agentPayload?.toolsAllow;\nif (agentPayloadToolsAllow && agentPayloadToolsAllow.length > 0) {\n  const normalizedAllow = expandToolGroups(agentPayloadToolsAllow).map((t) =>\n    normalizeToolName(t),\n  );\n  const requestsWebSearch =\n    normalizedAllow.includes(\"*\") || normalizedAllow.includes(\"web_search\");\n  if (requestsWebSearch) {\n    const webSearchProviders = listWebSearchProviders({ config: cfgWithAgentDefaults });\n    if (webSearchProviders.length === 0) {\n      preflightDiagnostics = normalizeCronRunDiagnostics({ /* warn entry */ });\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `preflightDiagnostics` field is added to `PreparedCronRunContext` and merged into the final result after `finalizeCronRun`:\n\n```ts\nconst result = prepared.context.preflightDiagnostics\n  ? {\n      ...finalized,\n      diagnostics: mergeCronRunDiagnostics(\n        prepared.context.preflightDiagnostics,\n        finalized.diagnostics,\n      ),\n    }\n  : finalized;\n```\n\nTypeScript compilation (`npx tsc --noEmit`) passes with no errors introduced by this change.\n\n_AI-assisted (Claude Sonnet, architecture and implementation review)_",
        "branch": "fix/cron-tools-allow-search-provider-check",
